        <!-- Section 10: Summary -->
        <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-indigo-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-indigo-400 pl-4">The Key Takeaways for Startup Founders</h2>

        <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-3">
          <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-gray-700 bg-gray-900/30">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-indigo-400 font-bold">1.</span> <strong class="text-white">Speed matters.</strong> Fast sites get crawled faster. Cloudflare Workers gives you sub-200ms globally for free. Google rewards performance.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-gray-700 bg-gray-900/30">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-indigo-400 font-bold">2.</span> <strong class="text-white">Consistency beats bursts.</strong> Publishing 15 pages/day for 8 weeks beats publishing 500 pages in one day. Google trusts consistent activity from new domains.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-gray-700 bg-gray-900/30">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-indigo-400 font-bold">3.</span> <strong class="text-white">Structured data is non-negotiable.</strong> FAQPage schema, Article schema, breadcrumbs — on every page. Google uses these to understand your content's type and quality.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-gray-700 bg-gray-900/30">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-indigo-400 font-bold">4.</span> <strong class="text-white">Internal linking drives discovery.</strong> Google finds pages by following links. Dense internal linking means faster discovery of new content.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-gray-700 bg-gray-900/30">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-indigo-400 font-bold">5.</span> <strong class="text-white">Backlinks are overrated for new sites.</strong> Zero backlinks, 744 pages indexed. Technical excellence and content quality matter more in 2026 than link-building for getting indexed.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-gray-700 bg-gray-900/30">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-indigo-400 font-bold">6.</span> <strong class="text-white">Thin content is worse than no content.</strong> One excellent 1000-word article beats five 200-word stubs. Google indexes quality, not quantity.</p>
          </div>
